  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Peel</strong> and finely dice the onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Slice</strong> the celery down the centre, lengthways, then finely dice</p>\r\n<p><strong>Peel</strong> and chop the garlic roughly</p>\r\n<p><strong>Slice</strong> the cherry tomatoes in half</p>\r\n<p><strong>Boil</strong> a kettle</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/628.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/628.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/628.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/628.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/628.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Add</strong> the rice, a pinch of salt and pepper and 350ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [700ml]</span> water to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once</strong> boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once</strong> cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/628.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/628.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/628.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/628.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/628.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Heat</strong> a large, wide-based pan with a matching lid (preferably non-stick) with 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [3 tbsp]</span> vegetable oil over a medium-high heat</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once</strong> hot, add the onion and celery and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to brown</p>\r\n<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, chop the thyme leaves and stalks finely, throwing away any woody parts</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/628.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/628.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/628.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/628.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/628.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Add</strong> the garlic, oregano, cumin, thyme and tomatoes with a generous pinch of salt and pepper and cook for a further 1-2 min</p>\r\n<p><strong>Transfer</strong> the contents of the pan to a bowl and set aside&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Wipe</strong> out the pan carefully with kitchen paper and return it to a high heat with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> vegetable oil</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/628.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/628.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/628.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/628.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/628.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Pat</strong> the haddock fillets dry with kitchen towel and season on both sides with salt and pepper</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once</strong> your pan is very hot, add the haddock&nbsp;and cook on one side for 2 min</p>\r\n<p><strong>Turn</strong> the haddock then cook for a further 2-3 min, then remove from the heat (your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily)</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/628.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/628.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/628.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/628.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/628.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, submerge the coriander in boiled water for 10 seconds (this is called blanching) then shake off the excess water and set aside to cool</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once</strong> cooled, chop the coriander finely then grind with a pinch of salt and pepper in a pestle and mortar to form a smooth paste</p>\r\n<p><strong>Add&nbsp;</strong>3 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [6 tbsp]</span> olive oil and mix well - this is your coriander oil</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/628.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/628.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/628.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/628.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/628.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Once</strong> your rice has finished cooking, stir the&nbsp;cooked vegetables and tomatoes into the rice&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
